@using SFA.DAS.ApprenticeCommitments.Web.Services.OuterApi;

<p>
    These roles and responsibilities set out what is expected of your training provider.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>They have:</strong>
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">

    <li>reviewed and kept a copy of the apprenticeship agreement, signed by you and your employer</li>

    @if (Model.DeliveryModel.Equals(DeliveryModel.PortableFlexiJob))
    {
        <li>discussed with you how your portable flexi-job apprenticeship will be delivered</li>
    }
    
    <li>ensured that your training plan accounts for prior learning, English and maths needs, and additional learning support</li>
    <li>told you and your employer your apprenticeship training start and end dates</li>
    <li>explained how off-the-job training will be delivered</li>
    <li>told you and your employer if they will use sub-contracted training providers to deliver any of your training </li>
    <li>explained that you will be assessed by an independent assessment organisation</li>

</ul>

<p>
    <strong>They will: </strong>
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">

    <li>manage the quality and delivery of your off-the-job training, and make sure it is recorded</li>

    @if (Model.DeliveryModel.Equals(DeliveryModel.PortableFlexiJob))
    {
        <li>support you in finding jobs as you progress through your apprenticeship</li>
    }

    <li>take responsibility for progress reviews between all parties every 12 weeks</li>

    @if (Model.DeliveryModel.Equals(DeliveryModel.PortableFlexiJob))
    {
        <li>make sure that you and each employer can see a summary of your learning and progress to date</li>
    }

    <li>let you and your employer know how to raise concerns or complaints about your training</li>

</ul>